reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Finally, my perfect gym bag!
reviews.reviewText: I had very particular wants in a gym bag - it needed to have a separate shoe compartment, an adjustable shoulder strap, and a wet compartment. Most importantly, it needed to be small - I don’t carry that much, but most of the bags with a shoe compartment are huge, so it’s been a process to find one that ticked all the boxes.This bag is great - it’s small and compact, has very nice detailing in the fabric and shiny metal hardware & zippers. The main (larger) compartment has a big zippered pocket and smaller slip pockets inside, and is where the shoe pocket is contained from the outside, so if you have shoes in the shoe pocket, naturally that would take up some of the space. Again, not an issue for me personally. The 2nd compartment has a (presumably waterproof, I haven’t tried pouring water in it to see if it holds) lining. I usually put my water bottle in that side in case it leaks. It’s not a huge pocket and I doubt it’s large enough to hold a towel, but would definitely hold a wet bathing suit, washcloth, or shampoo bottles.There’s also a slip pocket outside (would be nice if it were zippered, but that’s ok). Some details I’ve seen on other bags that would make this even better would be a mesh outside pocket on one end, the outside pocket to be zippered, and a tab to keep the hand straps together, but these are small. All in all, I’m really happy with this bag and highly recommend!
